Package albums

Class Collection

  • java.lang.Object
    • albums.Collection
  • public class Collection
extends java.lang.Object
    Container class defines the array list data structure to hold the album collection.
    Author:
    David Halim, Stephen Juan.

    • Constructor Detail

      • Collection

        public Collection()
        Default constructor initializes size of albums array to DEFAULT_SIZE. DEFAULT_SIZE is a static final int = 10. Calls the Overloaded constructor passing the value DEFAULT_SIZE. Initializes numAlbums = 0 (empty collection).

      • Collection

        public Collection​(int albumsSize)
        Overloaded constructor initializes size of albums array and numAlbums. Initializes size of albums array to an accepted value albumsSize. Initializes numAlbums = 0 (empty collection).
        Parameters:
        albumsSize - accepted value for size of albums array.

        Returns:

      • grow

        private void grow()
        increase the capacity of the array list by 4

      • add

        public boolean add​(Album album)
        Adds an album to the collection. Calls find(album) to make sure the new does not exist in the array to eliminate duplicates.
        Parameters:
        album - to add to the collection
        Returns:
        true if the add is successful, false if the album already exists in the collection.

      • remove

        public boolean remove​(Album album)
        Removes an album from the collection. Calls find(album) to get the index to remove. Maintains the current sequence of albums in the array after the deletion.
        Parameters:
        album - to remove from the collection.
        Returns:
        true if the remove is successful, false if the album does not exist in the class.

        Returns:

      • mergeByGenre

        private void mergeByGenre​(int first,

        Merges 2 sublists and sort them in the order of Genre.
        Parameters:
        first - - index of the first element of the right sublist to be merged
        middlePoint - - index of the last element of the right sublist to be merged
        last - - index of the last element of the left sublist to be merged

      • sort

        private void sort​(int first,
                  int last,
                  int sortingType)
        Recursive sort method that sorts the list using merge sort. Splits the every list/sublist into 2 halves until the lists reach size 1. It merges in the order of ReleaseDate or Genre according to int sortingType.
        Parameters:
        first - - index of the first element of the list/sublist to be sorted
        last - - index of the last element of the list/sublist to be sorted
        sortingType - represents the type of merge sorting; 0 = mergeByReleaseDate 1 = mergeByGenre.
